Minor: Longevity, Aging and Generational Studies Minor
Program_Policies: A grade of C or better is required for all courses in the minor, as specified by Senate Policy 59-10. In addition, at least six credits of the minor must be unique from the prescribed courses required by a student's major(s).; Note: With faculty approval, students may apply credits earned through special topics courses (297, 497), independent study or research that focus on aging or old age towards minor requirements.
